<noinclude>
This template creates a structured tutorial header with metadata.

== Usage ==
<pre>
{{Tutorial
|title = Tutorial Title
|author = Author Name
|difficulty = beginner/intermediate/advanced
|estimated_time = 30 minutes
|prerequisites = Basic Git knowledge
|topics = GitHub Actions, CI/CD
}}
</pre>

== Parameters ==
* '''title''': The title of the tutorial
* '''author''': The author(s) of the tutorial
* '''difficulty''': The difficulty level (beginner, intermediate, or advanced)
* '''estimated_time''': Estimated time to complete the tutorial
* '''prerequisites''' (optional): Prerequisites needed
* '''topics''' (optional): Topics covered in the tutorial

</noinclude><includeonly><div style="background: #f8f9fa; border: 1px solid #a2a9b1; border-radius: 5px; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 20px;">
<div style="font-size: 1.4em; font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #333;">{{{title|Tutorial}}}</div>
<div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: auto 1fr; gap: 8px; font-size: 0.95em;">
<span style="font-weight: bold;">Author:</span> <span>{{{author|Not specified}}}</span>
<span style="font-weight: bold;">Difficulty:</span> <span style="padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 3px; background: {{#switch: {{{difficulty|}}}
| beginner = #e8f5e9; color: #2e7d32
| intermediate = #fff3e0; color: #f57c00
| advanced = #fce4ec; color: #c2185b
| #default = #f5f5f5; color: #666
}}">{{{difficulty|Not specified}}}</span>
<span style="font-weight: bold;">Time:</span> <span>⏱️ {{{estimated_time|Not specified}}}</span>
{{#if: {{{prerequisites|}}} |
<span style="font-weight: bold;">Prerequisites:</span> <span>{{{prerequisites}}}</span>
}}
{{#if: {{{topics|}}} |
<span style="font-weight: bold;">Topics:</span> <span>{{{topics}}}</span>
}}
</div>
</div></includeonly>
